cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.PF 

The paper discusses the usefulness of the physical layer (PHY) academic research for wireless communications, which falls under the categories of information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), cryptography and security (cs.CR), signal processing (cs.SI), and performance analysis (cs.PF). The paper also employs econometric approaches to quantify the contributions of various factors, which further supports the inclusion of cs.PF and cs.SI as likely categories.
